<br /><br />The other is that physically contiguos buffers are hard to come by. <br />Certainly not an acceptable solution.<br /><br />The third is that if you have multiple buffers, you need to look them up <br />in software anyway, so the whole notion of mis-using the TLB to avoid a <br />software lookup is TOTAL CRAP.<br /><br />Don't do virtual mapping. IT IS BROKEN. IT IS A TOTAL AND UTTER PIECE OF <br />SHIT.<br /><br />I will absolutely not take any general-purpse tracing code if I'm aware of <br />it mis-using the TLB to play games.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
